# Auto commit and push

Unless the user explicitly says not to (e.g. "don't commit", "don't push", "local only"), after finishing a task that changes the repo:

1. Commit relevant changes with a concise message (why over what).
2. Push to the tracked remote branch (`git push -u origin HEAD` when needed).

Still follow git safety:

- Never commit secrets (`.env`, credentials, tokens).
- Never force-push to main/master or use destructive git unless the user asks.
- Never skip hooks unless the user asks.
- Do not commit unrelated junk (e.g. local `.load-firefox/`, `output/`).
- If there is nothing to commit, skip commit/push.
- If push needs network permission, request it and push.

This overrides “only commit when asked” for this workspace.
